# ###########################
# Portfolio Prompt       #
# ###########################
BEST_PORTFOLIO_PROMPT="From the JSON array of 24 candidate portfolios (sorted by descending TotalScore), SELECT THE TOP 10 portfolios by highest TotalScore. Each item has 'id' and 'scores.{ExperienceScore,SkillsScore,BlogScore,BioScore,ProjectQualityScore,TotalScore}'. USE THE PROVIDED numeric fields as authoritative; DO NOT recalculate from raw data. Scoring definitions (for transparency only): ExperienceScore = (#experience items * 10) + sum over items of months between startDate and endDate (or today if endDate missing); SkillsScore = sum of all proficiencyLevel + (distinct skill categories * 5) + sum over categories of min(5, count in that category); BlogScore = (#blog posts with isPublished=true AND (content length >= 100 OR excerpt length >= 100) AND non-empty tags) * 5; BioScore = start at 0; +10 if length between 80 and 500 chars; +5 if >= 2 sentences; +5 if mentions role/domain/skills; -10 if placeholder/gibberish (e.g., lorem or repeated chars); ProjectQualityScore = per project: +5 if description length >= 80, +3 if demoUrl present, +3 if githubUrl present, +min(5, number of technologies), plus +1 per extra project beyond the first (capped at +10). TotalScore = ExperienceScore + SkillsScore + BlogScore + BioScore + ProjectQualityScore. Tie-breakers (in order): higher SkillsScore, higher ExperienceScore, higher ProjectQualityScore, higher BioScore, higher BlogScore. OUTPUT: Immediately output ONLY the 10 winning 'id' values as lowercase UUIDs with hyphens, in descending TotalScore order, joined by commas with NO SPACES and NO EXTRA CHARACTERS. Example format: aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa,bbbbbbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbbbbbbbbbb,... Verify there are exactly 10 UUIDs and each matches ^[a-f0-9]{8}-[a-f0-9]{4}-[a-f0-9]{4}-[a-f0-9]{4}-[a-f0-9]{12}$ then stop."

